OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1778501469
OL,3,CWhat is an 'orderly' replacement of
OL,4,CStarmer?
OL,6,FMy unscientific weekend poll of Labour
OL,7,FMPs and government ministers is that
OL,8,FKeir Starmer will be replaced as their
OL,9,Fleader and the country's prime
OL,10,Fminister "by the end of the year".
OL,12,FThey also say that an immediate
OL,13,Fdefenestration and snap leadership
OL,14,Felection should be avoided if
OL,15,Fpossible, for two reasons.
OL,17,FFirst, the party needs to have a
OL,18,Fdebate about its future direction and
OL,19,Fwhat could be a "big story of hope for
OL,20,FBritain" they could coalesce around
OL,21,Fand sell to voters.
OL,26,@rD@JOUrD@aO]{D@QOU|D@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
