PN,31302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1778501469
OL,3,CWhat is an 'orderly' replacement of
OL,4,CStarmer?
OL,6,FSecond, the leadership change should
OL,7,Fbe orderly, respectful and likely to
OL,8,Fyield a stable outcome.
OL,10,FThis means, they say, that the process
OL,11,Fneeds to be long enough to allow Andy
OL,12,FBurnham the opportunity to resign as
OL,13,Fmayor of Greater Manchester and
OL,14,Fcontest a by-election.
OL,16,FWhich is not to say they all want
OL,17,FBurnham as Britain's next prime
OL,18,Fminister. Some do. Some don't.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1778501469
OL,3,CWhat is an 'orderly' replacement of
OL,4,CStarmer?
OL,6,FWhat it means is they fear he and his
OL,7,Fsupporters would never cease to lobby
OL,8,Fto be Labour leader, and therefore no
OL,9,Fnew leader would be secure, unless
OL,10,FBurnham was given the opportunity to
OL,11,Fwin a leadership contest or crash and
OL,12,Fburn.
OL,14,F"If Andy feels he is blocked again,
OL,15,Fany new leader will be toast before
OL,16,Fthe next election," one senior MP said
OL,17,Fto me.
OL,26,@vD@AOUxD@SO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1778501469
OL,3,CWhat is an 'orderly' replacement of
OL,4,CStarmer?
OL,6,FAnd to give Burnham the rope he wants,
OL,7,Fthe leadership contest has to be
OL,8,Fdelayed till the autumn, say his
OL,9,Ffriends and foes.
OL,11,FI have two other pieces of
OL,12,Fintelligence, or perhaps more properly
OL,13,Funintelligence.
OL,15,FNo MP or minister is able to explain
OL,16,Fto me how this "orderly" transition to
OL,17,Fa new leader would actually transpire,
OL,18,Fif the PM were to dig in and refuse to
OL,19,Fleave - which right now Starmer shows
OL,20,Fevery sign of doing.
OL,26,@xD@POUxD@XO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
