OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1778501469
OL,3,CWhat is an 'orderly' replacement of
OL,4,CStarmer?
OL,6,FThere is a chance that the cabinet
OL,7,Fwould unite against him and
OL,8,Fcollectively make him an offer, to go
OL,9,Fwith dignity on a set timetable, that
OL,10,Fhe could not refuse.
OL,12,FMinisters are as we speak talking to
OL,13,Feach other about just such a scenario.
OL,15,FBut that would be to believe they are
OL,16,Fcapable of sublimating their
OL,17,Findividual personal ambitions and
OL,18,Fenjoyment of high office for what they
OL,19,Fwill see as a nebulous greater good.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
